    "index": 150,
    "title": "God’s Most Beautiful Names (Asmā’ Allāh al-Ḥusnā)",
    "slug": "gods-most-beautiful-names-asma-allah-al-husna",
    "bodyHtml": "<p>Each Divine Name Is a Unique Marker of God’s Ineffable &amp; Impenetrable Essence. God has ninety-nine special Names, but His Names are infinite in number. God’s Names Are Central to Islamic Spirituality &amp; Metaphysics. God’s Most Beautiful Names Bridge the Phenomenal &amp; the Non-Phenomenal, they are the keys to the Unseen. God’s Divine Names Reveal the Metaprinciples Instantiated in All Created Things. God has Names of Essence (<em>Asmā’ al-Dhāt</em>), Names of Attributions (<em>Asmā’ al-Ṣifāt</em>) and Names of Actions (<em>Asmā’ al-Af‘āl</em>)</p>"
